-- Peru Stocks: Candente Copper, Credicorp, Volcan Advance
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-31T21:59:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/peru-stocks-candente-copper-credicorp-volcan-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the market close.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.6 percent to 20,997.56. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 0.5 percent to 2,681.20.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, jumped 8.2 percent to 66 cents after receiving
government authorization to drill at its copper property.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, gained 2.5 percent to $124.15, in line with gains by
its New York-traded American Depositary Receipt and U.S. banks.
Its Banco de Credito unit said today it brokered Peru’s first
swap contract in soles.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1)  (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
and silver producer, advanced 1 percent to 3.08 soles after its
weighting was increased in Peru’s  exchange-traded fund , spurring
investors to add the stock to their portfolios, said Inteligo
SAB analyst Lali Merino.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
